com.vernalis.pdbconnector2.graphql

Class GraphQLQuery

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vernalis.pdbconnector2.graphql.GraphQLQuery
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GraphQL

    public class GraphQLQuery
extends java.lang.Object
implements GraphQL
    This is the top level GraphQL query container and is the entry point to most query construction. For the simple query 
     query TestQuery {
   human(id: "1000"){
     name
     height
   }
 }
    The following code: 
     GraphQLQuery query = new GraphQLQuery("TestQuery");
 query.addField("human.name");
 query.addField("human.height");
 query.getField("human").addArgument(GraphQLArgument.of("id", "1000"));
    Since:
    1.28.0
    Author:
    S.Roughley knime@vernalis.com
